DESCRIPTION:<p><em>The Fear of 13</em> tells the extraordinary true story 
 of Nick Yarris\, who spends more than two decades on death row for a murde
 r he insists he did not commit. Through a series of prison visits with a v
 olunteer named Jackie\, Nick traces a life shaped by impulse and consequen
 ce. As Nick and Jackie&rsquo\;s conversations deepen\, the line between wi
 tness and participant blurs\, forcing both to confront what justice demand
 s\, what belief requires\, and the perilous distance between true freedom 
 and the illusion of self-determination. By turns devastating\, darkly funn
 y\, and life-affirming\, <em>The Fear of 13</em> is a powerful exploration
  of truth and trust\, conscience and connection.<br /><br />After an accla
 imed run in London\, two-time Academy Award&reg\; winner Adrien Brody make
 s his Broadway debut in an &ldquo\;unmissable portrait of death row injust
 ice&rdquo\; (<em>The Telegraph</em>). Nominated for Best New Play at the O
 livier Awards\, with Brody also earning a nomination for Best Actor\, <em>
 The Fear of 13</em> is based on the extraordinary true story of Nick Yarri
 s. Written by Lindsey Ferrentino (<em>Ugly Lies the Bone</em>) and directe
 d by Tony Award&trade\; winner David Cromer (<em>Good Night\, and Good Luc
 k</em>)\, this gripping exploration of truth\, justice\, and the chasm bet
 ween them will leave you hanging on every word.</p>
LOCATION:James Earl Jones Theatre\, 138 West 48th Street\, New York NY 100
 36
END:VEVENT
